---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionTag from '../../components/ui/SectionTag.astro';
import Button from '../../components/ui/Button.astro';

const post = {
  title: "Local SEO in 2026: What's Changed and What Still Works",
  category: 'SEO',
  publishedAt: 'January 14, 2026',
  excerpt: 'The tactics that have faded and the fundamentals that keep driving rankings for service businesses.',
};
---

<BaseLayout title={`${post.title} — Railshop Blog`} description={post.excerpt}>

  <div class="breadcrumb">
    <div class="container breadcrumb-inner">
      <a href="/blog" class="breadcrumb-link">Blog</a>
      <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
      <span class="breadcrumb-current">{post.title}</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="post-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="post-hero-meta">
        <span class="post-cat-tag">{post.category}</span>
        <span class="post-date">{post.publishedAt}</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="post-title">{post.title}</h1>
      <p class="post-byline">By the Railshop Team</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="content-wrap">
    <div class="container content-grid">

      <article class="post-body">
        <p>Local SEO has changed a lot in the past few years. Some of the tactics that worked reliably in 2022 and 2023 have faded. Others have gotten more important. If you're running a service business and trying to figure out what's actually worth your time, here's our honest read on where things stand.</p>

        <h2>What's Changed</h2>
        <p>Directory submissions and basic citation building used to move the needle on their own. Today they're table stakes — necessary but not sufficient. Google has gotten much better at understanding local intent, and the bar for appearing in the local pack has risen considerably in most competitive service categories.</p>
        <p>Keyword stuffing in your Google Business Profile description is also less effective than it used to be. Google's gotten better at ignoring it, and it makes your listing look like it was written by a bot — which doesn't help when a prospect is deciding who to call.</p>
        <p>AI-generated content published at scale is another one that's running out of road. We've seen several service businesses chase volume with thin AI content and get hit with ranking drops. Google is getting better at identifying low-value content, and in local search especially, trust signals matter more than volume.</p>

        <h2>What Still Works</h2>
        <p>Service area pages built around real local intent — not just city name plus service keyword — are still one of the highest-leverage moves in local SEO. When done right, they capture demand that broad pages miss entirely.</p>
        <p>Your Google Business Profile is still one of the most important assets you have. Regular updates, accurate categories, responding to reviews, and posting occasionally all contribute to how Google perceives your relevance and activity. Most businesses set it up once and never touch it again. That's a missed opportunity.</p>
        <p>Reviews remain a major ranking factor and conversion driver. A consistent process for generating reviews from happy customers — not a one-time push — compounds over time. The businesses we work with that have strong review velocity consistently outperform competitors with more links and more content.</p>
        <p>Internal linking and site structure matter more than most people realize. If Google can't easily understand what services you offer and where you offer them, it won't rank you for those terms regardless of how good your off-page signals are.</p>

        <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>
        <p>Local SEO in 2026 rewards businesses that invest in their digital presence consistently over time — not ones chasing shortcuts. The fundamentals haven't changed: be relevant, be trusted, be active. The tactics for executing those fundamentals have evolved, but the underlying logic hasn't.</p>
        <p>If you want a clear picture of where your local SEO stands and what's worth addressing first, <a href="/contact#hubspot-meetings">book a call</a>. We'll give you a straight answer.</p>
      </article>

      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <p class="sidebar-eyebrow">About the Authors</p>
          <p class="sidebar-body">Railshop is a boutique digital growth agency for service businesses. Everything we publish comes from direct experience managing paid media, SEO, and web programs for clients across HVAC, landscaping, home security, and more.</p>
          <a href="/about" class="sidebar-link">Meet the team →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <p class="sidebar-eyebrow sidebar-eyebrow--blue">Work With Us</p>
          <p class="sidebar-body">Book a no-commitment call to discuss your digital program and see what's possible.</p>
          <a href="/contact#hubspot-meetings" class="sidebar-btn-link">Book a Call</a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="cta-banner">
    <div class="cta-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <SectionTag label="Enjoyed This Post?" />
      <h2 class="cta-title">See how we put this into practice.</h2>
      <p class="cta-desc">Book a call to talk through your digital program.</p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <Button href="/contact#hubspot-meetings" variant="primary">Book a Call</Button>
        <Button href="/blog" variant="secondary">Read More Posts</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .breadcrumb { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--surface); }
  .breadcrumb-inner { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; padding: 14px 24px; font-size: 13px; }
  .breadcrumb-link { color: var(--text-3); transition: color 0.15s; }
  .breadcrumb-link:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .breadcrumb-sep { color: var(--border-2); }
  .breadcrumb-current { color: var(--text-3); overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap; max-width: 360px; }

  .post-hero { padding: 64px 0 56px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .post-hero-meta { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 20px; }

  .post-cat-tag { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--blue); background: var(--blue-glow); border: 1px solid var(--blue-border); border-radius: 999px; padding: 4px 10px; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; }
  .post-date { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text-3); }
  .post-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 48px); font-weight: 800; color: var(--text-2); letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.15; max-width: 720px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .post-byline { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-3); }

  .content-wrap { padding: 64px 0 80px; }
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px; gap: 64px; align-items: start; }

  .post-body { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-3); line-height: 1.85; min-width: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
  .post-body h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-2); margin-top: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .post-body p { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-3); line-height: 1.85; }
  .post-body a { color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }

  .sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; position: sticky; top: 88px; }
  .sidebar-card { background: var(--surface-2); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
  .sidebar-eyebrow { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-3); }
  .sidebar-eyebrow--blue { color: var(--blue); }
  .sidebar-body { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-3); line-height: 1.7; }
  .sidebar-link { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none; }
  .sidebar-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .sidebar-btn-link { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: var(--blue); color: #111315; font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 18px; transition: opacity 0.2s; text-decoration: none; margin-top: 4px; }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .sidebar-btn-link { color: #FFFFFF; }
  .sidebar-btn-link:hover { opacity: 0.88; }

  .cta-banner { position: relative; background: var(--surface); border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 80px 0; overflow: hidden; }
  .cta-glow { position: absolute; top: -80px; right: -80px; width: 500px; height: 400px; background: radial-gradient(ellipse, rgba(56, 182, 255, 0.07) 0%, transparent 70%); pointer-events: none; }
  .cta-inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; text-align: center; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 16px; }
  .cta-title { font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 40px); font-weight: 800; color: var(--text-2); letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.2; max-width: 560px; }
  .cta-desc { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-3); max-width: 440px; line-height: 1.7; }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; margin-top: 8px; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .sidebar { position: static; }
  }
</style>
